cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a new method for subspace clustering, which is a problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper uses linear algebra and optimization techniques to construct a physically meaningful affinity matrix. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for representation-based subspace clustering, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
